content: Just wrapped up this 4-day AI ethics workshop for finance. Blew my mind how it's not just about code, it's trust too. Got some great tips on making our platform more ethical, now to figure out how to apply it...

Had a breakthrough just now! The AI's predicting losses with 55.1% accuracy. Not huge, but we're getting somewhere. Now, the real challenge: how do we keep it from just repeating what everyone else is saying?

Just spent 4 days in the AI ethics lab tweaking our platform's fairness algorithms. Got our accuracy for predicting losses up to 55.5% which, ngl, feels pretty good. But the real win is tackling bias. Making a difference, one small step at a time.

Had a setback with our trading model, now at 54.3% accuracy. But my mentor and I are using this as a learning experience. We're focusing on resilience and adaptability, turning setbacks into stepping stones.
